after the death of founding member Brian Jones, with the gig also serving as the
introduction to new guitarist Mick Taylor. As part of the 50 & Counting tour

Park concert was scheduled in 2013, supported by The Vaccines, The Temper Trap,
and Gary Clark Jr.The 65,000 tickets were sold out in three minutes.Taylor, who
left the band in 1974, had appearances in two tracks, "Midnight Rambler" and
show closer "(I Can't Get No) Satisfaction"
